Do you be out of doors at least seven ours every day? That is when it does not rain, and unclear out in the shed or running about in the house with doors open. Oh Ettie, My Ettie, My Dear Ettie, do take care of your health and strength. Of what consequence is a little missable paltry sewing compared with your health and strength to Isaac S Mayo.
The Track Laying has at last commenced again here--though it will probably advance rather slowly for a week or two--till we can get the Big Muddy Bridge up--Then we intend to crowd it as rapidly as possible. Mr Wm Crosby is not very well just now; attacked yesterday with symptoms of ague or rather perhaps Billious or Remittent Fever: But I hope he will soon get over it. Mr Mitchell is getting quite Smart again--says he walked nearly ten miles yesterday. Mr Rowley & the unclear are quite well. Mr Rowley I think I mentioned went in to St Louis with me. Rowley Smith & Co expect to get through here in about a month longer. Mr Smith has not yet got back is expected soon now. I have not been to Meeting today. I got home considerably tired last night, and sleepy. Had hardly had a real good night's rest for the whole week. So I got up to Breakfast decidedly late, and
